{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YZEJHcYgptWUWbpVxmAaVE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: query-layer-discipline\n     3→description: Scaffold queryset/manager/selector layers and wire view reads through selector entrypoints with jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Query Layer Discipline (Jig)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill to standardize read paths through QuerySet + selector layers.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `model_name`\n    13→- `queryset_name`\n    14→- `manager_name`\n    15→- `selector_name`\n    16→- `selector_file`\n    17→- `view_name`\n    18→\n    19→## Usage\n    20→\n    21→```bash\n    22→jig run ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR:-.claude/skills/query-layer-discipline}/recipe.yaml --vars '{\n    23→  \"model_name\": \"Entity\",\n    24→  \"queryset_name\": \"EntityQuerySet\",\n    25→  \"manager_name\": \"EntityManager\",\n    26→  \"selector_name\": \"select_active_entities\",\n    27→  \"selector_file\": \"selectors.py\",\n    28→  \"view_name\": \"entity_list\"\n    29→}'\n    30→```\n    31→\n    32→If jig fails, use rendered snippets from stderr as manual patch guidance.\n    33→\n    34→Notes:\n    35→- The recipe now targets the rendered `model_name` and `view_name` selectors directly.\n    36→- `regex_escape` is applied inside regex-bearing anchors so symbol values are treated literally.\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d716adde-d93f-4371-9efb-26d5f3544144","uuid":"fabdebcf-9e79-4968-859a-50e535973d20"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TDhSZCMvLvQrQ32YQDQFZw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→name: query-layer-discipline\n     2→description: Introduce queryset, manager, and selector scaffolding for disciplined reads\n     3→\n     4→variables:\n     5→  model_name:\n     6→    type: string\n     7→    required: true\n     8→  queryset_name:\n     9→    type: string\n    10→    required: true\n    11→  manager_name:\n    12→    type: string\n    13→    required: true\n    14→  selector_name:\n    15→    type: string\n    16→    required: true\n    17→  selector_file:\n    18→    type: string\n    19→    required: true\n    20→  view_name:\n    21→    type: string\n    22→    required: true\n    23→  models_file:\n    24→    type: string\n    25→    required: false\n    26→    default: models.py\n    27→  views_file:\n    28→    type: string\n    29→    required: false\n    30→    default: views.py\n    31→\n    32→files:\n    33→  - template: templates/queryset_manager.py.j2\n    34→    inject: \"{{ models_file }}\"\n    35→    before: \"^class \"\n    36→    skip_if: \"class {{ queryset_name }}\"\n    37→\n    38→  - template: templates/manager_attr.py.j2\n    39→    patch: \"{{ models_file }}\"\n    40→    anchor:\n    41→      pattern: \"^class {{ model_name | regex_escape }}\\\\(\"\n    42→      scope: class_body\n    43→      position: before\n    44→    skip_if: \"objects = {{ manager_name }}()\"\n    45→\n    46→  - template: templates/selectors_header.py.j2\n    47→    to: \"{{ selector_file }}\"\n    48→    skip_if_exists: true\n    49→\n    50→  - template: templates/selector_fn.py.j2\n    51→    inject: \"{{ selector_file }}\"\n    52→    append: true\n    53→    skip_if: \"def {{ selector_name }}\"\n    54→\n    55→  - template: templates/views_import.py.j2\n    56→    inject: \"{{ views_file }}\"\n    57→    after: '^from \\.models import'\n    58→    at: last\n    59→    skip_if: \"from .{{ selector_file | replace('.py', '') }} import {{ selector_name }}\"\n    60→\n    61→  - template: templates/selector_call.py.j2\n    62→    patch: \"{{ views_file }}\"\n    63→    anchor:\n    64→      pattern: \"^def {{ view_name | regex_escape }}\\\\(\"\n    65→      scope: function_body\n    66→      position: before\n    67→    skip_if: \"{{ selector_name }}(\"\n    68→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d716adde-d93f-4371-9efb-26d5f3544144","uuid":"d7c1d1e3-67cf-47d8-a4a9-a8df2f0b3f5f"}
